  "market_context": "USD chart showing a week where Monday expanded higher then Tuesday formed a reversal candle. The analyst was waiting for a new swing point to form before trading away from the last swing, with weekly bias bullish if a midweek low could be confirmed.",
  "key_observation": "Wednesday formed a candle 2 closure after a bearish expansion reversed out of a point of interest, and the 1H chart showed a change in state of delivery, confirming the weekly low and aligning daily, weekly, and hourly time frames for bullish bias.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified that no new swing point had formed yet and waited for one before trading away from the last swing.",
    "Step 2: Observed Monday expanding bearish/higher and Tuesday forming a reversal candle, anticipating Wednesday to trade lower into a fair value gap to form a swing point.",
    "Step 3: Confirmed Wednesday's bearish expansion reversed out of a point of interest, producing a candle 2 closure on the daily.",
    "Step 4: Asked whether this daily swing point would form the weekly low on the weekly time frame.",
    "Step 5: Dropped to the 1H time frame to check for a change in state of delivery and confirmed it was present.",
    "Step 6: Aligned weekly (green anticipated), daily (green anticipated), and hourly (CISD) for two days of bullish bias.",
    "Step 7: Observed Thursday continuation with strong closure, then Friday continuation reaching into previous day high and higher."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded higher on Thursday with a strong closure and continued on Friday, reaching previous day high and higher as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "Anticipating a weekly low requires a daily candle 2 closure at a point of interest confirmed by an hourly change in state of delivery. Aligning weekly, daily, and hourly time frames provides multiple days of high-probability directional bias.",
